<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:23PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern
Gallatin County through 400 PM MDT...
At 322 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northeast of Belgrade, or 19 miles north of Bozeman, moving
north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain, winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern
Gallatin County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
